article_title: CDC survey of Americans finds long-term COVID symptoms an 'emerging public health concern'
meta_description: A new report from the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC) finds long-term symptoms in COVID-19 patients represents an "emerging public health concern. " The agency conducted a nationwide survey of adults 18 and over to compare the prevalence of long-term symptoms among those who have tested positive compared to those who have not tested positive. They found 2/3rds of those who tested positive reported long-term symptoms lasting over 4 weeks.
